headline: Amphenol beats results estimates on demand from datacom, defense sectors
summary: The Wallingford, Connecticut-based company's shares rose 2.5% in early trading.  Businesses eager to adopt artificial intelligence technologies, as well as governments boosting their defense budgets in response to rising geopolitical tensions, are driving demand for the company's connectors and sensors.  Amphenol makes interconnect systems, sensors and antennas used in automotive, industrial, defense and other sectors.
